---

## Why this works

A subsequence only cares about **relative order**.

So for every character in `s`, we try to find it in `t` from left to right.

If we find all characters in order, return `True`.

Otherwise, return `False`.

---

## Complexity

```python
Time: O(len(t))
Space: O(1)
```

We scan through `t` once.
